<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-03-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="490" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Knight</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-03-07"><hi rend="italic">March
                                        7, 1896</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 74.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose for transmission to Mr. J. C.
                            Manion, consular agent at Johannesburg, a copy of a telegram from Mr.
                            Hammond, one of the Americans under arrest at Johannesburg, expressing
                            his appreciation of Mr. Manion’s efforts in his behalf, and saying that
                            he is well treated by the Transvaal Government.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill.</hi><lb/><hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No.
                                74.—Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hammond</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Johannesburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-03-04"><hi rend="italic">March 4, 1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Please record my appreciation of Consul Manion’s efforts my behalf.
                                He has shown zeal and good judgment; rendering me great service. Am
                                well treated by Government. Preliminary trial next week. I have no
                                fear ultimate result, as I am innocent of attempt to overthrow
                                Government, though participated in reform movement.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hammond.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>